@Database CFG_NODELIST

@Index HBBS:Docs/Misc/Index.guide/MAIN

@Node Main "HBBS:Nodes/NodeList - Config File"

  Description:

  The HBBS:Nodes/NodeList file defines the paths for each node

  Options:

  NodeLocation_XX=<path>            @{" More... " link NodeLocation_XX}
  NodeDescription_XX=<string>       @{" More... " link NodeDescription_XX}
  AutoStart_XX=<boolean>            @{" More... " link AutoStart_XX}

@EndNode

@Node NodeLocation_XX "HBBS:Nodes/NodeList - NodeLocation_XX"

  NodeLocation_XX=<path>

    E.G.

    NodeLocation_1=HBBS:Nodes/Node1
    NodeLocation_2=HBBS:Nodes/Node2

    No Default, MUST be set!

    Specifies Location of the Node directory (in which logs are created, file
    uploaded etc, etc..)

    We recomend you use the settings in the example as it makes your life a
    bit easier and your BBS more structured,  This option was put in so that
    you can run a multinode BBS using two networked computers (parnet/sernet)
    as some sysops like to do (Hi Cruise! :-)

    Note: The UploadLog.txt and DownloadLog.TXT are created in this directory
    if enabled.

@EndNode

@Node AutoStart_XX "HBBS:Nodes/NodeList - AutoStart_XX"

  AutoStart_XX=<boolean>

    E.G.

    AutoStart_1=NO
    AutoStart_2=YES

    No Default, Must be set for each node that you have.

    This tells control wehter or not to start each node when control itself
    is started.

    Same as /X's IDLENODE option.

@EndNode

@Node NodeDescription_XX "HBBS:Nodes/NodeList - NodeDescription_XX"

  NodeDescription_XX=<string>

    E.G.

    NodeDescription_0=Local
    NodeDescription_1=Modem
    NodeDescription_2=Telnet

    Defaults to "Node XX" if not specified.

    Control displays the first 10 chars instead of "Node xx" in it's window
    for each node that you specify a description for.

@EndNode


